d.c: OUT! Australia draw first blood! Starc spears in a length ball around off, it's sharp and takes the shoulder of the bat as Moeen tries to heave it across the line. He ends up miscuing it in the air towards mid on where Bailey takes the catch safely.

OUT! Marsh strikes! He delivers a full ball on middle, Ballance flicks it across the line off his pads but fails to keep it down. It goes straight to short mid-wicket where Finch makes no mistake. Good sharp reflexive catch by Finchy!

OUT! Body blow for England as their man in form takes a walk to the pavilion. Marsh spears in a full ball around off, Bell swings his bat across the line and fails to keep his shot down. It goes aerially to deep mid-wicket and Starc covers good ground to his left from deep square leg to take the catch.

OUT! Two in two for Marsh! England are in deep, deep trouble now! Marsh digs in a short ball and Root tries to turn it on the leg side. He closes the face of the bat a tad early and it catches the top edge. The ball balloons behind the stumps, Haddin runs back and takes the skier to perfection.

OUT! Haddin takes a stunner! Short of a length ball on middle and off, Morgan stays in his crease and goes for the pull. The ball goes off the bottom edge and towards the keeper where he dives to his left and takes a one-handed catch. Morgan out for a duck once again and another wicket for Mitchell Marsh!

OUT! Maiden 5-wicket haul for Marsh! He is absolutely delighted and what a stunning catch by Steven Smith! Fullish ball on off, Buttler plays a full-blooded cover drive through the line but fails to keep it down. Smith manning the short extra cover region reacts quickly and takes the catch flying to his left. That's a ripper!

OUT! Johnson breaks the frustrating stand for Australia. He angles across a full length ball around off, Woakes tries to chip it over covers but it comes quickly onto the bat and he ends up mistiming it in the air towards mid off. Steven Smith takes the simplest of catches this time.

OUT! Sound of timber! Fast and furious delivery, full and in the line of the stumps, hint of reverse there as well, it's too quick for Broad, he tries to defend but is late in bringing his bat down. The stumps are shattered and the crowd erupts in joy. Golden duck!
OUT! Johnson bangs in a short ball, targeting the rib-cage of the batsman, Finn stays back to fend at it and chips it in the air. Johnson accepts the return catch gleefully. End is nigh for England.

OUT! Drama! Some controversy but Anderson is given run out. Fullish ball on middle and leg, sliding down, Taylor tries to flick but misses. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal and the finger goes up. Taylor is immediate to take the DRS and the replays confirm that it was missing leg. The decision is overruled but from here the controversy started. Here is what happened - While the fielders were appealing for the lbw, Anderson was outside the crease. The finger went up and after that there was a direct hit at the bowler's end. Of course, in the replays Anderson was found short of the crease but the argument was that once the umpire gave Taylor out, the ball became dead. Not sure what exactly prompted umpire Dharmasena to give Anderson out. A brave knock by the little man, Taylor and he is unfortunate not to get his maiden ODI ton. Australia win by 111 runs!

d.c: OUT! Bowled 'em! Full and swinging back into Warner, he tries to work it to the leg side but misses. The ball brushes his pads before hitting the stumps. First blood for the English. Warner gets a good start and throws it away. He was dropped on 11 but could not build on it.

OUT! Two in two! Watson goes for a golden duck! Slightly over-pitched and Watson looks to defend but the away moment takes the outside edge of his bat. Buttler does the rest behind the stumps. Another failure for Watto!

OUT! Timber! Fuller around off, Smith gets his front leg forward and looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the stumps. Woakes is celebrating for this huge wicket and the Aussie crowd looks in shock! Australians are struggling here and they need someone to stay with Finch.

OUT! Finch's stay is cut short by a direct hit! It seemed like the only way he could be dismissed today. A full ball outside off, Finch pushes it wide of mid off to the fielder's left. Bailey sets off in a trice and Finch responds but then half-way through he gives up. Eoin Morgan gets to the ball, takes aim and scores a bull's eye at the bowler's end. End of a magnificent knock, the MCG gives a standing ovation to Finch.

OUT! Played on! Finn roars as Bailey exits. On a good length outside off, Bailey looks to run it down to third man but is too close to the ball. Ends up chopping it on to the stumps off the bottom edge. He was just beginning to look good. England back in this. They have picked up both the set batsmen.

OUT! Marsh holes out! Finn delivers a length ball outside off, Marsh swings his arms with the intention of going big over long off. This time he gets more elevation than distance and Root takes the catch safely. End of an entertaining knock!

OUT! A good catch! A full ball outside off, Haddin gives this his all, swings with full might, but only gets a leading edge which goes all the way to third man. Stuart Broad comes running in and dives to take a good catch. An unselfish innings comes to an end.

OUT! Ho ho ho! If the previous one was good, this was even better! Maxwell departs to a stunning catch by Root. Full outside off, Maxwell gives himself room to the leg side and smashes it down to long off. Joe Root gets across to his right and throws himself to his right, plucking an absolute stunner. That ends a brilliant innings from another Victorian.

OUT! It is a hat-trick and a 5-fer for Finn! What a moment for Finn! A length ball outside off, Johnson backs away to the leg side and looks to smash it over the top but only succeeds in giving a catch to James Anderson at mid off. A century and a hat-trick on the opening day of the World Cup on the same day. Need anything more?
